{"title_page": "Raja Shivchatrapati", "text_new": "{{short description|Marathi Television show}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Raja Shivchatrapati<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/popular-historical-show-raja-shivchatrapati-to-return-on-the-audiences-demand/articleshow/74935697.cms</ref>\n| image                    = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = History\n| creator                  = Nitin Chandrakant Desai\n| based_on                 = Raja Shivchatrapati novel of [[Babasaheb Purandare]]\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Hemant Devdhar\n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = {{plainlist|\n* Amol Kolhe\n* Mrunal Kulkarni\n}}\n| narrated                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = Jay Bhavani Jay Shivaji by [[Ajay-Atul]]\n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = Ajay-Atul\n| country                  = India\n| language                 = Marathi\n| num_seasons              = One\n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = [[Nitin Chandrakant Desai]]\n| editor                   = \n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = Multi camara set-up\n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = \n| distributor              = \n| network                  = [[Star Pravah]]\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = November 2008\n| last_aired               = \n| website                  = \n| production_website       = \n| location                 = ND studios , Mumbai, Maharashtra , India.\n| channel                  = [[Star Pravah]]\n}}\n'''Raja Shivchatrapati''' is a historical TV serial based on [[Chatrapati Shivaji Maharaj]], the emperor and founder of the [[Maratha Empire]] in India. The program was first aired on Star Pravah, a Marathi TV channel, and was the first program aired on Star Pravah.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lokmat.com/television/raja-shivchatrapati-marathi-serial-start-again-star-pravah-gda/|title=\u0932\u094b\u0915\u093e\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0939\u093e\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0935 \u092a\u0941\u0928\u094d\u0939\u093e \u092d\u0947\u091f\u0940\u0932\u093e \u092f\u0947\u0923\u093e\u0930 '\u0930\u093e\u091c\u093e \u0936\u093f\u0935\u091b\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u0924\u0940', \u0935\u093e\u091a\u093e \u0938\u0935\u093f\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0930|last=|first=|date=2020-04-02|website=Lokmat|language=mr-IN|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> It is a popular historical serial<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/popular-historical-show-raja-shivchatrapati-to-return-on-the-audiences-demand/articleshow/74935697.cms|title=Popular historical show 'Raja Shivchatrapati' to return on the audience demand.|date=1 April 2020|work=Times Of India|access-date=6 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It is based on Raja Shivchatrapati, novel of Babasaheb Purandare. The program was created by Nitin Chandrakant Desai. The serial was re-broadcast from 3 April 2020 onwards on viewers popular demand during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/popular-historical-show-raja-shivchatrapati-to-return-on-the-audiences-demand/articleshow/74935697.cms|title=Popular historical show returns on TV on popular viewers demand.|date=2 April 2020|work=Times Of India|access-date=6 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nChatrapati Shivaji Maharaj, born at Shivneri fort, establishes  the Maratha kingdom against all odds by fighting against the Mughal dynasty.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Amol Kolhe]] as Chatrapati Shivaji Maharaj\n* Mrunal Kulkarni as Raj mata Jija Bai\n* Avinash Narkar as Shahajiraje Bhosale<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/popular-historical-show-raja-shivchatrapati-to-return-on-the-audiences-demand/articleshow/74935697.cms|title=Raja Shivchatrapati back on Television.|date=6 April 2020|work=Times Of India|access-date=6 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Yatin Karyekar as Aurangzeb\n\n== Production ==\nThe program was created and produced by Hindi film's art director Nitin Chandrakant Desai. Amol Kolhe played lead role of Chatrapati Shivaji Maharaj and Mrunal Kulkarni as Rajmata Jijabai.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Pote|first=Saumitra|url=https://marathi.abplive.com/entertainment/raja-shiv-chhatrapati-and-aambhatgod-serial-to-meet-again-audience-on-star-pravah-756573|title=On peoples demand Raja Shivchatrapati gonna come on Star Pravah again.|date=1 April 2020|work=ABP Majha|access-date=6 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It was directed by Hemant Devdhar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/marathi/popular-historical-show-raja-shivchatrapati-to-return-on-the-audiences-demand/amp_articleshow/74935697.cms|title=Raja Shivchatrapati directed by Hemant Devdhar|date=1 April 2020|work=Times Of India|access-date=6 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming took place at [[ND Studios]] in Maharashtra. The program is based on the Raja Shivchatrapati novel of renowned historian Babasaheb Purandare.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{:Category:India}}\n\n[[Category:Indian TV show]]\n[[Category:Maharashtra]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Marathi Television show}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Raja Shivchatrapati<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/popular-historical-show-raja-shivchatrapati-to-return-on-the-audiences-demand/articleshow/74935697.cms</ref>\n| image                    = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = History\n| creator                  = Nitin Chandrakant Desai\n| based_